# ğŸŒ Global Earthquake Visualizer

A Python project that fetches earthquake data (GeoJSON format) and visualizes it on an interactive world map using **Plotly**.  
Earthquakes are displayed as points, with **marker size representing magnitude** and **colors indicating intensity**.

---

## ğŸš€ Features
- Reads raw GeoJSON earthquake data.
- Cleans and saves a readable version of the dataset.
- Extracts **longitude, latitude, magnitude, and title** from each earthquake.
- Plots earthquakes on a **world map with interactive zoom & hover tooltips**.
- Magnitude controls **marker size** and **color intensity**.

